== Overview

You have landed at the main documentation page for http://lsdtopotools.github.io/[*LSDTopoTools*]. *LSDTopoTools* is a software package that is used to analyse topography for applications in hydrology, geomorphology, soil science and ecology. The software began within the https://www.geos.ed.ac.uk/geosciences/research/research-institutes/global-change/land-surface-dynamics[Land Surface Dynamics group] at the https://www.ed.ac.uk/geosciences/[University of Edinburgh], and now has developers and users around the world. 

The documentation is organised into a series of websites, listed below in the <<LSDTopoTools documentation topics>> section.

== Where is all the code?

The code lives as a series of repositories on https://github.com[Github]. 

The repositories are here: https://github.com/LSDtopotools

